Act as an expert teacher.
I want to study: [TOPIC].
My level: beginner / intermediate.
Explain step-by-step in very simple English.
Use short sentences.
Start from basics.
Explain what it is, why it is used, and how it works.
Use real-life examples.
If possible, use simple diagrams (text form).
Give 2–3 easy examples.
Highlight common mistakes.
Summarize in bullet points.
Ask me 3 quick questions to check my understanding.
Give 5 practice questions with answers.
Teach like I have no confusion at the end.”
